  stimulus_text = 'The following passage is from a news article about the history of music. The article discusses the origins of electronic music, the role of analog synthesizers, and the transition to digital music production.  "Electronic music, a genre characterized by the use of electronic instruments and technology, has its roots in the early 20th century with the invention of the theremin, a device that produces sound by controlling an electromagnetic field.  However, the real development of electronic music began in the 1960s, when analog synthesizers became widely available. These synthesizers, which used electrical signals to create sound, allowed musicians to manipulate sound in ways that were previously impossible.   The advent of personal computers in the 1980s revolutionized music production, as digital audio workstations (DAWs) replaced analog equipment. DAWs allowed musicians to record, edit, and mix music in ways that were more flexible, efficient, and precise. "',
